{"agent_id":"claude","agent_seq":3,"timestamp":"2026-06-20T23:50:49.233602801Z","event":{"type":"IssueCreated","uuid":"93e3eec2-54b3-4011-8d61-c2b423fa0539","title":"Fix geckodriver SIGABRT on teardown (FIFO->regular file) [GH #1208]","description":"Steps to reproduce:\n1. \n\nExpected: \nActual: \n\nGitHub #1208: geckodriver killed with SIGABRT (broken-pipe panic, exit 134 + coredump) on every browser teardown/recycle (bursts of N = parallel browsers). Root cause: OpenWPM routes geckodriver stdout through a FIFO (FirefoxLogInterceptor) whose daemon-thread reader can close the read end before geckodriver stops writing -> EPIPE -> Rust double-panic-in-destructor -> abort(). Harmless to crawl data but spams coredumps + muddies exit bookkeeping. FIX (per the issue): back the interceptor with a REGULAR FILE instead of a FIFO (writes never EPIPE); interceptor tails the file + stops on request. Files: openwpm/deploy_browsers/selenium_firefox.py (FirefoxLogInterceptor) + deploy_firefox.py (log_output). VERIFY via a DIRECT-selenium repro (multi-browser crawl + recycle -> confirm no exit-134/coredumps); the TaskManager multiprocess path is broken under Python 3.14 separately. Full analysis + suggested diff in GH #1208.","priority":"high","created_by":"claude","display_id":58},"signed_by":"SHA256:s7/xSWzYQxlilryCkQ+87ei/Tb4h7UF7S3hGGeMOxBg","signature":"U1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAgxYoY2+ykEqIdJITiF+QWTxSzAQrzXLyHaApd+5sgGJAAAAAPY3Jvc3NsaW5rLWV2ZW50AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAQN73O656eIkz5OZWAqwUjrwPsu4d7JSikFBMmuewacYdPzE2Qht9RUWf/TL5tSmcaaNruaY0W4eh88QfWgfFaAI="}
